 I agree...if the data would need to be accessed externally, then make the getters public.
If not, then just test what IS public.
-Eric

  Mark Meyers &lt;markm@...&gt; wrote: you should use &quot;some.package.MyClass.TestMyClass.class&quot;

But I don&#39;t like the mixing of production and test code.
There is no need for static inner class here as far as I can see.
Just make it an &quot;external&quot; class, and if you need to access getter and
setter methods, make them public...


&gt; -----Original Message-----
&gt; From: sansanwo [mailto:sansan@...]
&gt; Sent: dinsdag 12 februari 2002 12:22
